events.body:
@leofidus: I assume that it will be possible to use the bitcoind through SPV (so the P2P network) and RPC (for progress queries, and managing).
If step 3 is left out, there would be indeed an intermediate phase in which the wallet _embeds_ bitcoind as a library just as it does now. Then only the project layouts would change.

@int03h: No changes to RPC interface are needed for this apart from a split. The walletd would implement the wallet side of the RPCs, bitcoind would implement the blockchain/query part of the RPCs. 
For backward compatibility with clients that assume both are in the same process, the walletd could act as a proxy for those commands.
